# Get info

npm info <package-name>



# Install package

npm i <npm-package>@beta or @latest or @version



# Publish a version

version is a commit number
push tag to github to do so
tags will be associated with releases


git tag 1.0.0
git push --tags



# Publish new change

Do change
semantic versioning "version" : breakingChange.newFeature.patchBugFix - e.g. 1.1.0
commit
add tag
push to github
push tag to github
npm publish



# Push as a beta

change
semantic versioning e.g. 1.2.0-beta.0
commit
add tag e.g. 1.2.0-beta.0
push to github
push tag
npm publish --tag beta

When beta version is finished we remove the -beta.0 meta data and push the changes
